
ijktable.cxx and ijktable.h contain a set of C++ classes and routines for
generating isosurface patches in convex polyhedra in arbitrary
dimensions.  They construct the isosurface patch as a subset of the
convex hull of a subset of polyhedra vertices and edge midpoints.
(See ``Isosurface construction in any dimension using convex hulls''
by P. Bhaniramka, R. Wenger, and R. Crawfis, IEEE Trans. on Vis. and
Computer Graphics, 10 2004, pp. 130-141, and "Isosurfacing in higher
Dimensions" by P. Bhaniramka, R. Wenger, and R. Crawfis,
Visualization, 2000, Salt Lake City Utah: IEEE Computer Society
Press.)

Source code includes K. Clarkson's program hull for generating convex hulls.

Programs:

ijkgentable: Generate isosurface tables in various dimensions.
ijkdifftable: Output the difference of two isosurface tables.
ijktableinfo: Output isosurface table information.


Source files:

ijkgentable.cxx, ijkgentable.h: Main program for generating isosurface tables.

ijkgenpatch.cxx, ijkgenpatch.h: Generate isosurface patch for a given
  table entry.

ijktable.cxx, ijktable.h: Class ISOSURFACE_TABLE for storing isosurface tables.

ijkxitIO.cxx, ijkxitIO.h: I/O routines for .xit files (XML format).

clarkson_hull.c, clarkson_hull.h: Kenneth Clarkson's convex hull routines
  for building convex hull in arbitrary dimensions.

ijkdifftable.cxx: Main program for outputting the difference of two
  isosurface tables.


Author:

